==English==
===Etymology===
Pref. a- (for on or of) + far.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈfaɹ/

===Adverb===
'''afar'''
# At, to, or from a great distance; far away; &mdash; often used  with from preceding, or off following; as, he was seen from  afar; I saw him afar off.


